725301f-a.title: Queens: 39th Avenue - 59th Street
725301f-a.text:
39th Avenue, north side, east from 59th to 60th Streets, showiag old Woodside homes. 39th Avenue was formely known
as Riker Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  June 23, 1932

725302f-a.title: Queens: 39th Avenue - 59th Street
725302f-a.text:
39th Avenue, south side, between 59th and 60th Streets, seen from the former. This house was owned in 1891 by Mrs. Louisia. In rear are the high tension wires of the Long Island Railroad.
P. L. Sperr  June 23, 1932
